content.text:
Their mighty ones have sent their underlings for water;
They have come to the trenches and found no water.
They have returned with their vessels empty;
They have been put to shame and dishonored,
And they cover their heads.

The wild donkeys stand on the bare heights;
They pant for air like jackals;
Their eyes fail
For there is no vegetation.

Do not despise us, for Your own name’s sake;
Do not disgrace the throne of Your glory;
Remember and do not break Your covenant with us.
